Vivendi Income Jumps Most Since Listing, Pays First Dividend

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-04-08T10:26:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/vivendi-income-jumps-most-since-listing-pays-first-dividend.html
Vivendi Income Fund Ltd., a
commercial, retail and industrial property investor, rallied the
most since it listed in November after saying it will distribute
its maiden payment to shareholders.  The stock gained 29 cents, or 6.1 percent, to 5.01 rand at
12:25 p.m. in Johannesburg, the highest since Jan. 17.  Vivendi said it will pay out 9.96 cents per linked unit for
the first half through February.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sikonathi Mantshantsha in Johannesburg at 
 smantshantsh@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  